  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Farhat and Al-Taani [11] developed a rule-based system that could translate simple English sentences into Arabic with an accuracy of 85.71%.",
    "Similarly, Alawneh et al. [12] combined rule-based and example-based English-to-Arabic machine translation using parsing and a hybrid methodology to handle ordering and agreement.",
    "They evaluated their approach on 250 test samples, and the results achieved 97.2% precision on average.",
    "Also, Al-Rukban and Saudagar [13] evaluated three commercial English-to-Arabic systems, Google Translate, Bing Translator, and Golden Alwafi, and found that Golden Alwafi achieved the highest BLEU score, indicating the most human-like translations.",
    "Although rule-based methods are straightforward, they require extensive time to develop and maintain.Neural-driven methods, including those based on neural networks and PLMs, have become increasingly popular."
  ],
